cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper deals with information theory and coding, specifically achievable and converse bounds for general channels and mismatched decoding. This falls under the scope of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses the performance of codes with possible mismatched decoding metric, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of random coding and analysis of tightness could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the mention of the matched case and minimax meta-converse could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
